Download the latest version of Docker Compose:

bash
Copy code
sudo curl -L "https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/latest/download/docker-compose-$(uname -s)-$(uname -m)" -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
Set the executable permission for the downloaded binary:

bash
Copy code
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
Verify the installation by running the following command to check the version of Docker Compose:

css
Copy code
docker-compose --version
This should output the version of Docker Compose installed on your system.

Note: The above steps assume that your RHEL 7.9 system has access to the internet to download the necessary packages and dependencies.
